Qs I ask founders:
- What do you think about diversity? -> looking for them to volunteer in depth knowledge or action plan in place already

- Whats the biggest fight you had with your cofounder? -> testing honesty and cofounder dynamic
- what’s the biggest mistake you made founding your company? -> intentionally grilling them to see if they have high ego or not
- what’s your process for product iteration? -> understanding if they have shiny object synd

- what progress have you made with BD? -> being the founding Eng means they can take their hands off the wheel and refocus on sales (probs), they need to be good at selling 

happy to chat offline if you want! good luck :)
oh and I intentionally leave things vague to see if they give me the real honest answer I want

- if you eat before, it will prolong your trip
- not sure how tall or heavy you are, but adjust the dose accordingly. 2g if you’re on the smaller side, 3g if you’re larger 
- boil 2-3g in water and add lemon juice to reduce the taste 
- set your intentions before the trip, what you want to learn etc.

- have a trip sitter to help guide you and reassure you on the trip - this could be a trusted friend who can comfort you 
- do it on a Friday or Saturday, usually it lasts around 6-8 hours and you need emotional time (a day) to recover after 
- if it’s your first time, do it somewhere where you’re comfortable

- you’re gonna feel like throwing up in the first 30 min to one hour. This is normal. Just keep it down. 
- you’re going to see entities, beings, shapes, and colours. don’t be afraid they’re your friends! 
- have a good trip!!

why I prefer being an early employee over a founder:
- you get all the fun without any of the responsibility 
- you get to choose the areas of growth you enjoy 
- you share a great vision with people who inspire you everyday
- you get paid a good salary and equity 
- you can bet on 5 cos in 10 yrs instead of 1

it used to be this long excel sheet, but then I narrowed it down to three things: culture, pay, product. 

Culture: Is diversity a priority to them? 
Pay: Do they pay competitively? 
Product: Do I find it interesting or does it show signs of a billion dollar product? https://i.imgur.com/gbbUIYV.jpg
Why bet on 1 company exiting when you can bet on 5 😈
Yes, and the most difficult part is deciding which factors are most important to you specifically!
good idea !!

1. What does diversity look like at your company? -> I’m expecting equal gender ratio and racial diversity distributed equally top down, active initiatives with trackable numerical outcomes. E.G. I bring in 50/50 men/women eng candidates for hiring 

Cos have problems scaling past 10 if they’re not mindful of DEI

2. I ask the founders what their biggest mistake has been so far at their company. They respond in one of two ways: A. They defer and give me a BS response, which tells me that they’re high ego or B. They sit back and laugh and explain the many mistakes they made. 

Working with low ego folks is important to me!
